# NoomiBodi Project Context

AI-powered nutrition tracking app built with React Native (TypeScript), Supabase backend, and Claude API.

## Architecture

### Screens (src/screens/)
- **ChatTabScreen** — horizontal pager wrapping QuickLogPage (page 1) and ChatScreen (page 2)
- **QuickLogPage** — daily calories/macros, add meal photo, weight log, smart suggestions, today's meals
- **ChatScreen** — conversational interface with Claude, quick action chips, markdown rendering
- **MealsTabScreen** — horizontal pager wrapping MealsScreen (saved meals, page 1) and SharedMealsPage (page 2, with unread badge)
- **MealsScreen** — saved meals library with search, sort, macro filters, AI meal builder, share-with-friend via long-press
- **SharedMealsPage** — "Share a Meal" button (meal picker → friend picker flow), received meals inbox with add-to-library, collapsible "Shared by You" section showing sent meals, unread indicators
- **ReportsTabScreen** — horizontal pager wrapping ReportsScreen and InsightsPage
- **SocialScreen** — activity feed, pending friend requests (collapsible), sent requests (collapsible), friends list (horizontal scroll), weekly leaderboard; "Add Friend" opens AddFriendModal
- **AddFriendModal** — BottomSheet with user search, friendship status buttons (Follow/Pending/Accept/Friends)
- **FriendProfileScreen** — RootStack screen showing friend's profile, stats (hidden if private), remove friend action
- **ProfileTabScreen** — horizontal pager wrapping ProfilePage (page 1) and SettingsPage (page 2)
- **ProfilePage** — user profile picture, username, bio, stats (streak, days tracked, adherence), goals summary, "Edit Profile" button
- **SettingsPage** — privacy toggle, API key, appearance, sign out, reset profile
- **EditProfileScreen** — RootStack screen for editing username, display name, bio, profile picture upload
- **AdminDashboard** — admin-only tab with AI usage analytics (conditionally shown)
- **OnboardingScreen** — multi-step onboarding (API key, profile info, goals, activity, account, username, details, Claude plan); styles in separate `OnboardingScreen.styles.tsx` using `createStyles(colors, isDark)` pattern
- **SignInScreen** — standalone sign-in screen shown after sign-out (without profile reset); supports email/password, Apple, and Google sign-in
- **EmailVerificationScreen** — blocks entry to main app until email is verified; polls session every 5s, has resend with 60s cooldown; skipped for social sign-ins (Google/Apple)

### Services (src/services/)
- **claude.ts** — Anthropic Messages API integration, system prompts, response parsing, AI usage logging
- **claudeTools.ts** — RAG tool definitions + execution for Claude function calling
- **mealLog.ts** — daily_logs CRUD (Supabase + offline queue); triggers streak milestone check after successful log
- **savedMeals.ts** — saved_meals CRUD + `clearAllSavedMeals()` for profile reset
- **storage.ts** — AsyncStorage (API key, messages) + Supabase profiles/plans; `UserProfile` includes social fields (username, displayName, profilePictureUrl, bio, isPrivate); `clearUserProfile()` clears profiles, user_plans, daily_logs, weight_logs, user_insights
- **profileService.ts** — username validation, availability check, user search via `public_profiles` view (ILIKE on username/display_name), admin search via `profiles` (includes email/role), profile picture upload to Supabase Storage, partial profile field updates, `suggestUsernameFromEmail()`
- **friendships.ts** — friend request CRUD (send/accept/decline/remove); accept/decline restricted to recipient via `following_id` filter; queries for accepted friends, pending received/sent, friendship status check between two users
- **activityFeed.ts** — streak milestone insertion, duplicate checking, friend activity feed query (RLS handles privacy); `checkAndRecordMilestone()` for auto-logging milestones
- **leaderboard.ts** — weekly leaderboard calculation (adherence % = days hit calorie goal / 7); filters out private users; returns ranked list
- **sharedMeals.ts** — share meals with friends, inbox query (two-step: shared_meals + saved_meals/public_profiles), sent shares query, unread count, mark as read (recipient-only), delete (recipient-only), copy to saved meals
- **reportData.ts** — weight logs, daily summaries, overview stats
- **adminAnalytics.ts** — admin dashboard data queries
- **analytics.ts** — weight prediction, adherence patterns, correlations
- **insightGenerator.ts** — AI-generated insights via Claude
- **offlineStore.ts** — offline queue + read cache + `clearOfflineData()` for profile reset
- **supabase.ts** — Supabase client initialization
- **notifications.ts** — FCM token registration/unregistration, `sendNotification()` (invokes Edge Function), `sendMilestoneNotifications()`, `claim_device_token` RPC call for stale token cleanup
- **widgetBridge.ts** — native bridge to write widget data to App Group UserDefaults and reload WidgetKit timelines via `SharedGroupPreferences`
- **widgetDataSync.ts** — aggregates today's calories/macros from `daily_logs` and goals from `user_plans`, then calls `updateWidgetData()` to push to the widget

### iOS Widgets (ios/NoomiBodi Widget/)
Native WidgetKit extension written in Swift. Shares data with the main app via App Group `group.noomibodi` using `UserDefaults(suiteName:)` with key `widgetData` (JSON string).

**Widget types:**
- **Home screen small** (`systemSmall`) — calorie ring + consumed/goal text
- **Home screen medium** (`systemMedium`) — calorie ring with "+" button + protein/carbs/fat rows
- **Lock screen circular** (`accessoryCircular`) — calorie ring with remaining calories
- **Lock screen rectangular** (`accessoryRectangular`) — calories + protein/carbs/fat gauges
- **Control Center** — timer toggle (placeholder, not wired to nutrition data)
- **Live Activity** — Dynamic Island placeholder (not yet integrated)

**Data flow:** Meal logged → Supabase `daily_logs` → `syncWidgetData()` fetches today's totals + goals → `updateWidgetData()` writes JSON to App Group UserDefaults → `reloadWidgets()` triggers `WidgetCenter.shared.reloadAllTimelines()` → widget reads `widgetData` and refreshes.

**Sync call sites:** QuickLogPage (after meal log, weight log, offline sync), ChatScreen (after send/AI response), MealsScreen (after save), SmartRecommendations (after suggested meal log), offlineStore (after offline sync).

**Native bridge files:** `ios/SharedGroupPreferences.h` + `.m` (Obj-C React Native module exposing `set(suiteName, key, value)` and `reloadWidgets()`).

### Push Notifications (Firebase + Supabase Edge Function)
iOS push notifications via Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) → APNs.

**Notification types:**
- `friend_request` — when a user sends a friend request
- `friend_accepted` — when a recipient accepts a friend request
- `shared_meal` — when a friend shares a meal
- `streak_milestone` — when a friend hits a streak milestone (sent to all non-private accepted friends)

**Architecture:**
- **Client:** `@react-native-firebase/messaging` (modular API) for token management and message listeners
- **Server:** Supabase Edge Function `send-notification` (Deno) — validates caller JWT, looks up recipient FCM tokens from `device_tokens`, dispatches via FCM HTTP v1 API with Google service account JWT
- **Native:** `AppDelegate.swift` configures Firebase, implements `UNUserNotificationCenterDelegate` for foreground banners, clears badge on `applicationDidBecomeActive`

**Token lifecycle:** Register on app launch → upsert to `device_tokens` → refresh via `onTokenRefresh` listener → delete on sign-out → stale tokens cleaned via `claim_device_token()` RPC

**Call sites for `sendNotification()`:** AddFriendModal (friend_request, friend_accepted), SocialScreen (friend_accepted), SharedMealsPage (shared_meal), MealsScreen (shared_meal), mealLog.ts (streak_milestone via `sendMilestoneNotifications`)

**Edge Function secrets (Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets):** `FCM_PROJECT_ID`, `FCM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` (Firebase service account JSON), plus auto-injected `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`

**Deployment:** `supabase functions deploy send-notification --no-verify-jwt` (gateway JWT verification disabled; function validates JWT internally)

### Key Patterns
- **Theming**: `useTheme()` hook from `ThemeContext` — apply colors via inline styles `{ color: colors.text }`, not in StyleSheet.create. For screens with separate style files (OnboardingScreen), use `createStyles(colors, isDark)` function pattern with `useMemo`.
- **Auth**: `useAuth()` from `AuthContext` — wraps Supabase auth; provides `signIn`, `signUp`, `signInWithApple`, `signInWithGoogle`, `signOut`, `resetPassword`, `resendVerificationEmail`, `refreshSession`
- **Social Auth**: Apple Sign-In via `@invertase/react-native-apple-authentication` (library auto-hashes nonce with SHA256 before sending to Apple, so pass RAW nonce to both the library and Supabase); Google Sign-In via `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin` (patched native iOS code via `patch-package` to support nonce parameter; Google does NOT auto-hash, so pass SHA256 hashed nonce to Google + raw nonce to Supabase `signInWithIdToken`)
- **Identity Linking**: Supabase automatic linking is enabled by default — same email across Google, Apple, and email/password maps to one account
- **Email Verification**: After email/password sign-up, user completes onboarding but is blocked from the main app by `EmailVerificationScreen` until `email_confirmed_at` is set; social sign-ins skip this
- **App Navigation States**: `App.tsx` manages screen state as `'loading' | 'onboarding' | 'signIn' | 'emailVerification' | 'main'`; sign-out goes to `signIn`, profile reset goes to `onboarding`; `RootStack` includes `EditProfileScreen` and `FriendProfileScreen` as pushable screens on top of `MainTabs`
- **Social Features**: Bidirectional friendships (both must accept), privacy toggle (hides activity/leaderboard), streak milestones auto-logged on meal log, weekly leaderboard (Mon-Sun adherence %), meal sharing between accepted friends
- **Impersonation**: `ImpersonationContext` — admin-only session switching for testing other accounts; `ImpersonationBanner` red border when active; `ImpersonateModal` for admin dashboard search
- **Modals**: use `BottomSheet` component for consistent drag-to-dismiss, dark backdrop (AddFriendModal, FriendPickerModal, MealPickerModal, ImpersonateModal use this pattern)
- **Reusable components**: `ChatInputBox` (chat input with image attachment), `ThemedMarkdown` (themed markdown renderer used in chat, AI meal builder, quick log descriptions), `MealPickerModal` (select a meal from library for sharing), `FriendPickerModal` (select friends for sharing)
- **Profanity filter**: `src/utils/profanityFilter.ts` — client-side check for usernames/display names/bios; skipped for admin accounts
- **Push Notifications**: `useNotifications` hook in `App.tsx` — registers FCM token, listens for foreground/background messages, navigates on tap; `notifications.ts` service handles token CRUD and Edge Function invocation
- **Offline**: writes queued locally via `offlineStore.ts`, synced on reconnect via `useOfflineSync` hook
- **Day change**: `useDayChange` hook triggers refresh at midnight

## Conventions

- TypeScript strict, functional components only
- Styles via `StyleSheet.create` at bottom of file; theme colors applied inline in JSX
- For screens with separate style files, use `createStyles(colors: ThemeColors, isDark: boolean)` function that returns `StyleSheet.create({...})`, consumed via `useMemo` in the component
- `colors.surface` for card backgrounds, `colors.border` for card borders, `borderRadius: 14` for cards
- 12px spacing between sibling components on QuickLogPage
- All modals use `BottomSheet` wrapper (tap/drag dismiss, dark backdrop)
- Claude responses parsed with markers: `[MEAL_DATA]`, `[PLAN_START]`, `[SAVE_MEAL]`, `[PORTION]`
- AI usage logged to `ai_usage_logs` table after every Claude API call
- Onboarding and auth screens always follow system theme (ThemeProvider defaults to `mode: 'system'`)
- Primary buttons invert in dark mode: white bg with dark text (light mode: dark bg with white text)
- Apple Sign-In button inverts in dark mode (white bg/dark text); Google button stays blue in both themes

## Database (Supabase + RLS)
Tables: `profiles`, `user_plans`, `saved_meals`, `daily_logs`, `weight_logs`, `user_insights`, `ai_usage_logs`, `friendships`, `activity_feed`, `shared_meals`, `device_tokens`
Roles in `profiles.role`: `admin`, `beta`, `pro`, `standard`, `byok` (default)

**Social columns on `profiles`:** `username` (UNIQUE), `display_name`, `profile_picture_url`, `bio`, `is_private` (default false)

**Views:**
- `public_profiles` — security definer view exposing only safe columns (`id`, `username`, `display_name`, `profile_picture_url`, `bio`, `is_private`, `created_at`). All social cross-user lookups use this view. Excludes `email`, `gender`, `age`, `height_cm`, `current_weight_kg`, `activity_level`, `role`. GRANT to `authenticated`, REVOKE from `anon`/`public`.

**Social tables:**
- `friendships` — bidirectional friend system (follower_id, following_id, status: pending/accepted/declined). Both users can view/delete; only follower can create; only recipient (`following_id`) can accept/decline (UPDATE).
- `activity_feed` — user achievements (streak milestones). RLS enforces privacy: friends' activity visible only if friendship accepted AND `is_private = false`.
- `shared_meals` — share saved meals between friends (meal_id FK → saved_meals). Sender must own the meal; recipient can mark read/delete. `saved_meals` has an RLS policy allowing recipients to view shared meals.

**Push notification tables:**
- `device_tokens` — FCM token storage (user_id, fcm_token, platform). RLS: users manage own tokens. UNIQUE(user_id, fcm_token). ON DELETE CASCADE from auth.users.

**Helper functions:**
- `is_admin()` — SECURITY DEFINER function checking `profiles.role = 'admin'`, used in admin RLS policies to avoid recursion.
- `claim_device_token(p_fcm_token)` — SECURITY DEFINER function that deletes stale `device_tokens` entries for the same FCM token belonging to a different user. Called during token registration to handle device reuse across accounts.

**Storage bucket:** `profile-pictures` (public). Folder structure: `{user_id}/{timestamp}.jpg`. URLs stored in `profiles.profile_picture_url`.

See `docs/database_schema.md` for full schema, `docs/roles.md` for role details.

## Dependencies
- react-native-image-picker, react-native-chart-kit, react-native-svg
- react-native-markdown-display (chat + onboarding plan), @react-native-community/netinfo (offline)
- @supabase/supabase-js, axios, react-native-vector-icons/Ionicons
- @invertase/react-native-apple-authentication (Apple Sign-In)
- @react-native-google-signin/google-signin (Google Sign-In, patched via patch-package for iOS nonce support)
- @react-native-firebase/app, @react-native-firebase/messaging (push notifications via FCM; use modular API)
- js-sha256 (nonce hashing for Google Sign-In)
- patch-package (postinstall script applies native iOS patches)

## Sensitive Files (gitignored)
- `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.*.local` — environment secrets
- `ios/GoogleService-Info.plist` — Firebase config (API keys, project IDs)
- `supabase/.temp/` — Supabase CLI local state (project ref, pooler URL)
- `src/utils/testAccounts.ts`, `docs/seed_test_accounts.sql` — test credentials
